--- BookIt Backend Environment Configuration ---

1. Server Configuration

The port the Express server will run on (defaults to 5000 in server.js)

PORT=5000

2. Database Configuration (MANDATORY for Mongoose)

Replace the placeholder value below with your actual connection string

from MongoDB Atlas or your local MongoDB instance.

Structure: mongodb+srv://<user>:<password>@<cluster-name>/<database-name>?retryWrites=true&w=majority

MONGO_URI="mongodb+srv://user:password@cluster0.abcde.mongodb.net/BookItDB?retryWrites=true&w=majority"

3. Security (BEST PRACTICE)

A strong, random string used to sign JWTs (if you implement user authentication later).

You can generate a random string and place it here.

JWT_SECRET="your_very_long_and_random_secret_key"

4. Frontend URL (MANDATORY for CORS in production)

This is the domain of your deployed React frontend.

The 'cors' package uses this to restrict who can access your API.

FRONTEND_URL="http://localhost:3000"

(When deployed, this might be "https://www.google.com/search?q=https://bookit-frontend.vercel.app")